Today is the anniversary of the death of Gerolamo
\f1\b0  
\f0\b Cardano
\f1\b0  (1501-1576), Italian {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polymath"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 polymath}}, whose interests and proficiencies ranged from being a mathematician, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physician}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biologist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 biologist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 chemist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astrologer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 astrologer}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 astronomer}}, philosopher, writer, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gambler"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 gambler}}. \
He was one of the most influential mathematicians of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Renaissance"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Renaissance}}, and was one of the key figures in the foundation of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 probability}} and the earliest introducer of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_coefficients"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 binomial coefficients}} and the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_theorem"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 binomial theorem}} in the Western world. He wrote more than 200 works on science.\cb1 \
\cb3 Cardano partially invented and described several mechanical devices including the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combination_lock"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 combination lock}}, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimbal"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 gimbal}} consisting of three concentric rings allowing a supported {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compass"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 compass}} or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gyroscope"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 gyroscope}} to rotate freely, and the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Driveshaft"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Cardan shaft}} with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universal_joint"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 universal joints}}, which allows the transmission of rotary motion at various angles and is used in vehicles to this day. \cb1 \
\cb3 Today, he is well known for his achievements in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebra"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 algebra}}. He made the first systematic use of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negative_numbers"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 negative numbers}} in Europe, published with attribution the solutions of other mathematicians for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cubic_equation"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 cubic}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quartic_equation"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 quartic equations}}, and acknowledged the existence of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imaginary_number"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 imaginary numbers}}.\
\

